parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Airbag Failure and Inadequate Recall Response
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident, and the inadequate response to recalls can leave vehicles unrepaired, putting drivers and passengers at risk.
symptoms: Airbag light remains on
airbag failure to deploy
airbag deployment without impact
and passenger airbag off light illumination.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the concentric slave cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Headlight Failure Due to Burned or Corroded Wiring
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight wiring can cause the headlights to malfunction or not function at all, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Headlights do not turn on
dim or flickering headlights
exposed wiring
brittle or cracked wiring insulation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The melting or burning of the reflector bowl can cause the headlights to produce a reduced or distorted light output, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Dim or yellowish headlights
burned or melted reflector bowl
reduced light output
difficulty seeing at night.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tail lights can cause reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Tail lights do not turn on
dim or flickering tail lights
corroded or damaged tail light connectors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Airbag system failure can lead to accidents or injuries in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Airbag warning lamp remains on
passenger airbag status lamp is on
airbag failure message.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause loss of critical vehicle functions, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Instrument cluster lights turn off
all digital displays on cluster disappear
headlights and taillights turn off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Seat heater failure can cause burns or fires.
symptoms: Driver's seat back heater grid shorts
causing damage to insulation and leather seat cover
hot enough to cause physical burns.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Headlight failure can reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Bi-xenon headlights no longer light up the road
reflector bowls burn out over time
reducing headlight intensity.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Central locking system failure can cause doors to lock or unlock unexpectedly, trapping occupants or allowing unauthorized access.
symptoms: Door locks work intermittently
key fob and central lock button fail
doors lock with key fob but only driver's door unlocks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leaks can cause electrical system failures, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Water leaks into the center console
floor
and other areas
causing electrical problems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition coil failure can cause engine misfires, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Engine runs rough
"Service Engine Soon" light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Vehicle fires can cause injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle catches fire while driving
smoke comes out of the air ducts
gauges malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Heated Seat Malfunction and Fire Hazard
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the heated seat can cause burns, fires, and accidents, posing a significant risk to the driver's safety and well-being.
symptoms: The heated seat becomes extremely hot
causing burns to the driver's legs or buttocks
and may even ignite a fire. The seat may also emit a burning smell
and the leather may be damaged or burned through.
